# Firmware — SlimPad

KMK firmware written in CircuitPython for 12 switches + EC11 rotary encoder.

## Files
- `main.py` — main keyboard code

## Features
- **12 keys** with one-press shortcuts
- **Rotary encoder** — scroll through clipboard history (last 5 copied items)
- **Encoder click** — paste the selected clipboard entry
- **OLED display** — live preview of selected clipboard entry and position in history

## How clipboard history works
1. Press **COPY** key → sends Ctrl+C and saves entry to history
2. **Rotate encoder** left/right → scroll through last 5 copied items
3. **Click encoder** or press **PASTE** key → pastes the currently selected entry
4. OLED shows which entry is selected (e.g. `2/4`)

## Key Layout
```
┌──────────┬──────────┬──────────┐
│  COPY    │  PASTE   │  UNDO    │  ROW0
├──────────┼──────────┼──────────┤
│  SAVE    │ SAVE AS  │  REDO    │  ROW1
├──────────┼──────────┼──────────┤
│ SEL ALL  │  CUT     │  FIND    │  ROW2
├──────────┼──────────┼──────────┤
│  NEW     │  CLOSE   │  PSCR    │  ROW3
└──────────┴──────────┴──────────┘
```

## Pin Mapping
| XIAO Pin | Function |
|----------|----------|
| D0 | ROW0 |
| D1 | ROW1 |
| D2 | ROW2 |
| D3 | ROW3 |
| D6 | COL0 |
| D7 | COL1 |
| D8 | COL2 |
| D9 | ENC A |
| D10 | ENC B |
| MISO | OLED SDA |
| TX | OLED SCL |

## Installation
1. Download CircuitPython for XIAO RP2040:
   https://circuitpython.org/board/seeeduino_xiao_rp2040
2. Double-press BOOT button → BOOT drive appears
3. Copy `.uf2` file to BOOT drive → CIRCUITPY drive appears
4. Download KMK: https://github.com/KMKfw/kmk_firmware
5. Copy `kmk/` folder into `CIRCUITPY/lib/`
6. Copy `main.py` to root of `CIRCUITPY/`
7. Plug in and use!
